    mFileStrings[i] = listFile[i].getAbsolutePath();
    result = Integer.parseInt(mFileStrings[i]);  

I&#39;m really not sure why you thought that was going to work. Image resource integers only exist for resources in your app. For images in the filesystem, you could use `BitmapFactory`, but I really recommend just using Glide to make it easier.

