In your scenario [BottomNavigationView](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/support/design/widget/BottomNavigationView) can work, simply you need to enable/disable next buttons as per completion of current (First) button process.

Initially set all button disable except the first one by looping.

     private void enableBottomBar(){
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; mBottomMenu.getMenu().size(); i++) {
            if(i==0){
                mBottomMenu.getMenu().getItem(i).setEnabled(true);    
            }else{
                mBottomMenu.getMenu().getItem(i).setEnabled(false);
            }
            
        }
    }

Later you can enable the next buttons by passing position.

    private void enableBottomBar(boolean enable, int position){
        mBottomMenu.getMenu().getItem(position).setEnabled(enable);

    }

